cs.LO, cs.DB, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.CC 

The paper proposes a logic on words that has applications in information extraction and database theory, specifically in the form of document spanners. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of logic (cs.LO), databases (cs.DB), formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and computational complexity (cs.CC). The focus on finite models and efficient model checking also supports the inclusion of cs.CC and cs.DS among the likely categories.
